Class House

  • java.lang.Object
    • House
  • public class House
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a House which has a pyramidal roof and a base. The House contains many cuboidal rooms which are made of rectangular walls. The pyramidal roof has a rectangular base and triangular walls.
    Version:
    September 3, 2018
    Author:
    Shubhi Jain, Aviral Agrawal, Sarthak Moorjani

    • Field Detail

      • rooms

        public House.Cuboid[] rooms
        This is an array of Cuboids (rooms). It is initialized with maxNoOfRooms in the constructor. Each Cuboid represents a room.

      • houseTop

        public House.Pyramid houseTop
        This represents the roof of the House which is pyramidal in shape.

      • houseType

        private char houseType
        This represents the Type of the House. The House is commercial if the type is 'c' or it is residential if the type is 'r'.

      • countRooms

        private int countRooms
        This is used to maintain the count of the rooms in a House. The count increases by 1 everytime the constructor of Cuboid is called.

      • houseNumber

        private int houseNumber
        This represents the house number which is unique for each House.

      • baseLength

        private int baseLength
        This represents the length of the entire House inside which the rooms are constructed.

      • baseWidth

        private int baseWidth
        This represents the width of the entire House inside which the rooms are constructed.

      • height

        private int height
        This represents the height of the cuboidal part of the House, i.e. the height of the House excluding the roof. This height is same for all the rooms of the House.

      • pyramidHeight

        private int pyramidHeight
        This represents the height of the pyramidal roof of the House.

    • Constructor Detail

      • House

        public House​(int maxNoOfRooms,
             int houseNumber,
             int baseLength,
             int baseWidth,
             int height,
             int pyramidHeight,
             char houseType)
        Constructor for objects of class House. All variables are initialised with the values given.
        Parameters:
        maxNoOfRooms - The array rooms[] is initialised with maxNoOfRooms.
        houseNumber - specifies the houseNumber of the house.
        baseLength - Denotes the length of the base of the entire house
        baseWidth - Denotes the width of the base of the entire house
        height - Denotes the height of the base structure of the house. Note that height of each room is same
        pyramidHeight - Denotes the height of the pyramidal structure of the house
        houseType - Tells whether the house is residential or commercial

      • getBadWalls

        public int getBadWalls()
        This method aims to return the total number of bad walls in each room of the house. For example, if there are 2 rooms and both rooms have 4 bad walls, then return 8.
        Returns:
        Returns the total number of bad walls in each room of the house.

      • houseVolume

        public int houseVolume()
        The volume of the house is given by baseLength*baseWidth*height + volume of the pyramid
        Returns:
        Returns the volume of the house.

      • freeSpace

        public int freeSpace()
        The free space in the house is the unconstructed part of the base of the house. As mentioned in the lab statement it is possible that the entire house is not constructed that is the sum of volumes of all the rooms may not equal the volume of the base. So we want you to find the empty/freespace in the base of the house. Note that the free space does not include the pyramidal roof of the house.
        Returns:
        Returns the free space in the house.

      • getRent

        public int getRent()
        If the house is commercial then the revenue generated is the sum of the cost of each room in the house. If the house is residential then the revenue generated is the surfaceArea of the house.
        Returns:
        Returns the revenue generated by the house.

      • getHouseType

        public char getHouseType()
        This method returns the type of the house i.e. residential or commercial
        Returns:
        Returns the type of the house.

      • getSurfaceArea

        public int getSurfaceArea()
        Surface area of the house is generated as: 2*height*(baseLength+baseWidth) + surface area of the pyramidal roof.
        Returns:
        Returns the surface area of the house.
